description._content: Catalog #: 09_01968 Title: Waldeman P. Jahn Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Group shot of military personnel. Typewritten Inscription ""Left to Right. First Row: Cdr Honsinger - Capt Sapptington - Capt Haisten - Lcdr Borgardt - Capt Brower - Radm Bowen - Capt Talley - Lt Porter - Cdr Schuh - Capt Linnekin - Cdr Knick. Second Row: Cdr Stout - Cdr H.A. Smith - Cdr Tolbert - Cdr Galloway - Cdr Curtin - Cdr Wrocklage - Cdr Baggett - Cdr Cariker - Cdr King - Cdr Gibbs. Third Row: Cdr Waldeman P. Jahn - Cdr Bucklew - Lcdr Alsover - Cdr Capriotti - Lcdr Clark - Lcdr Haggquist - Lcdr Chesky - Lcdr Wachtel - Cdr Kleffner - Ens Perett. Fourth Row: Lcdr Nourse - Ens McArdle - Lcdr Wiseman - Lcdr Wyckoff - Lcdr Feltham - Lcdr Ratcliff - Lcdr Ricks - Lt Ault - Lcdr Rose - Lcdr Pendergraft - Lcdr Wilkinson - Lcdr Bartholemew - Lcdr Jameson. Back Row: Cdr Treadwell - Ltjg Schlecht - Dr. Cook - Lcdr Glennon - Lt Delong - Lt Weymouth - Lcdr Utterback - Lt Kelly - Ltcol Stein, Waldeman P. Jahn (b. 1920) was a Naval Aviator who served during World War II and became a Commander in the United States Navy. Tags: Waldeman P. Jahn Special Collection Photo Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
